hja@robocop.cs.hut.fi (Jari Helminen) writes:

>I would like to get information on DES on-chip implementations and
>their manufacturers. Also I would appreciate information on speed
>comparisions and method of usage. Does anyone have any experiences ?

Here the (european !) chips I know:

1. Cryptech CRY12C102

	22.5Mbit/s according to Data Sheet, with 32 Bit interface

	We use this one, because it was the only one available
	when we started the project. No problems !

	A week ago, I have heart that the company has some problems.

2. Pijnenburg PCC100

	20Mbit/s according to Data Sheet

	Address: PIJNENBURG B.V., Boxtelswweg 26, NL-5261 NE Vught,
	The Netherlands

3. INFOSYS DES Chip (Germany)

	S-Boxes must be loaded by software. So you can modify the
	Algorithm.

	Sorry, I don't have the data sheet handy. Please E-Mail me
	if you need further information.

